comments.body:
- using `std::string`:

```
$ cat a.h 
#include <string>
void f(std::string s) {}
$ cat test.cpp 
#include "a.h"
int main() { f("abc"); }
$ include-what-you-use test.cpp 

test.cpp should add these lines:
#include <string>  // for basic_string

test.cpp should remove these lines:

The full include-list for test.cpp:
#include <string>  // for basic_string
#include "a.h"     // for f
---
```

- using `std::string_view`:

```
$ cat a.h 
#include <string_view>
void f(std::string_view s) {}
$ cat test.cpp 
#include "a.h"
int main() { f("abc"); }
$ include-what-you-use test.cpp 

(test.cpp has correct #includes/fwd-decls)
```

